Study on Causes of Heart Disease
Smoking, obesity, unhealthy diet - there are risk factors for cardiovascular disease. But what really triggers a heart failure or a heart attack? Hamburg researchers now want to take a closer look at the genetics of 9,000 healthy and sick people.
By analyzing the genetics of 9,000 people, Hamburgers and Swiss scientists want to find out more in detail the causes of cardiovascular disease.
The research project is the largest of its kind in the German-speaking region, the University Hospital Hamburg-Eppendorf (UKE) announced on Friday. The Kühne Foundation supports the project with 12.5 million euros. From Switzerland, the high mountain hospital Davos, which belongs to the Foundation, and the University Hospital Zurich are involved.
